<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="582" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1940,2039]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,151,645]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="582" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,1940,1966]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Comment</emphasis>
. It was not possible to obtain male 
<typeStatus box="[670,772,1941,1967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">syntypes</typeStatus>
; however, based on the brief diagnosis presented in the description, and the illustrations and biology (
<bibRefCitation author="Heller, K. M." box="[649,790,1976,2002]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" pagination="52 - 54" refId="ref7004" refString="Heller, K. M. (1922) Springende Blutenkelche, verursacht durch ein neues Apion (Col.). Entomologische Mitteilungen, 11 (2), 52 - 54. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 3333" type="journal article" year="1922">Heller 1922</bibRefCitation>
), together with detailed examination of female 
<typeStatus box="[1331,1432,1977,2003]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">syntypes</typeStatus>
, this species is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Sousa &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" box="[530,666,2012,2038]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Pygidiapion" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zeppelinii">
<emphasis box="[530,666,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">P. zeppelinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the smaller size (length 
<quantity box="[975,1075,2012,2039]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.80 mm</quantity>
and maximum width 
<quantity box="[1320,1424,2012,2039]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" unit="mm" value="0.85">0.85 mm</quantity>
); brownish head, rostrum and antennae; scutellum subquadrate; and by association with 
<taxonomicName box="[1131,1245,151,177]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Dalbergia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1131,1245,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">Dalbergia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (
<taxonomicName box="[1314,1425,151,178]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
). Males would be needed for a more complete description and better separation from 
<emphasis box="[1090,1234,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Sousa &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" box="[1090,1229,187,213]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Pygidiapion" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zeppelinii">P. zeppelinii</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
